\f5 \cf0 Q.
\f3\b0  Why isn\'d5t Pester a full-featured calendar/scheduling program? What use is it otherwise?\
\

\f5\b A.
\f3\b0  I wrote and use Pester on my Mac for the same reason I use programs such as BigClock and TikTok on my Palm, the built-in clock on my Newton and the alarm on my cellular phone. Sometimes all you want is an alarm to go off in 5 minutes, not an \'d2appointment\'d3 or \'d2meeting\'d3 entry that survives in perpetuity and is synchronized with your phone, PDA and iPod. On the other hand, if you\'d5re happy with what you\'d5re using, stick with it.\
\

\f5\b Q.
\f3\b0  OK, but why doesn\'d5t Pester have feature 
\f7\i X
\f3\i0 ?\

\f5\b \
A.
\f3\b0  I didn\'d5t need it. I have looked at (and even registered) some similar programs such as Alarm Clock Pro, Alarm Clock S.E., CountDown, Tea Timer and the like. None of them did what I wanted. Please check out those other programs first; if Pester comes closest to your ideal but is missing a key feature, let me know and I\'d5ll consider adding it.\
\

